There's a reason and people are looking going.

42:08.866 --> 42:09.527
I know him.

42:09.547 --> 42:10.508
I know her.

42:11.009 --> 42:14.053
I think I know where this story truly is.

42:14.073 --> 42:22.486
In verse 16 through 19, so she kept his garment with her until his master came home.

42:23.146 --> 42:31.218
Then she spoke with him with words like these saying, the Hebrew servant whom you brought to us came into me to mock me.

42:31.810 --> 42:37.838
So it happened as I lifted my voice and cried out that he left his garment with me and fled outside.

42:38.479 --> 42:48.753
So it was when his master heard the words, which his wife spoke to him saying, your servant did to me as this manner that his anger was around.

42:48.773 --> 42:49.694
You see what she's doing?

42:49.934 --> 42:50.635
She's blaming him.

42:50.675 --> 42:51.657
It's your fault.

42:51.677 --> 42:52.638
You brought him here.

42:52.658 --> 42:56.684
She does what so many people will do, believers as well.

42:57.044 --> 42:58.546
She rehearses her story.

42:58.978 --> 42:59.759
over and over.

42:59.779 --> 43:01.843
I want to rehearse my story till he comes home.

43:02.163 --> 43:02.905
I'm going to rehearse.

43:02.965 --> 43:03.706
I'm going to rehearse.

43:04.007 --> 43:09.156
She blame shifts, puts it on the husband and then she's calling the other servants to rally.

43:09.636 --> 43:11.940
I'm going to rally all these people with my story.

43:11.960 --> 43:14.945
She just, of course, leaves out little pieces of the truth.

43:15.366 --> 43:19.593
And I think, well, I think he's angry because he knows her.

43:20.775 --> 43:22.258
I think that's why he's angry.

43:22.882 --> 43:24.626
You put me in this place.

43:24.846 --> 43:26.089
And so here he is.

43:26.149 --> 43:35.250
He's going to end up in the trowel, which brings us to our last point, whatever you do for the glory of God in trowels.

43:35.330 --> 43:41.680
trials or what God brings us into so that He might do this wonderful work in our lives.

43:42.121 --> 43:55.061
James 1-2, my brethren counted all joy when you fall into various trials knowing that the testing of your faith produces patience, but let patience have its perfect work that you may be perfect and complete and lacking nothing.

43:55.141 --> 43:58.066
God has a vision to fulfill.

43:58.466 --> 44:07.359
Through this man who was given this vision to follow and bring to pass Abraham, Isaac, Jacob will bring this great nation.

44:07.700 --> 44:22.002
So verse 20 we read, then Joseph's master took him, put him into prison, a place where the king's prisoners were confined and he was there in the prison.

44:23.904 --> 44:27.570
Note I think this.

44:28.866 --> 44:34.273
exceeds anything that he faced over all those days.

44:36.175 --> 44:56.882
I think one of the greatest supreme trials, and maybe this speaks to someone today, is when you've done right, you've been faithful, and you end up still yet not delivered, and your trial continues.

44:57.506 --> 45:01.010
David Goliath slazed a giant.

45:02.833 --> 45:09.581
The amazing thing about that is Israel's delivered into victory after the oppression of the Philistines.

45:11.043 --> 45:15.188
And you would think, Joseph, and don't we all think, you know, I did what was right.

45:15.408 --> 45:21.656
I stood and I battled and I fought and I came out victorious.

45:22.156 --> 45:26.642
I don't understand why I'm not being rewarded, if you would.

45:27.234 --> 45:37.123
why I'm not being put further, lifted out of prison, lifted out of the slavery that I'm in as the Joseph's relation.

45:37.404 --> 45:39.746
Instead, he ends up in prison.

45:40.447 --> 45:49.815
And I think one of the hardest supreme trials that you'll ever face, doing good and right and still not being delivered out of the moment.

45:50.856 --> 45:56.722
And when people bring false slanderous accusations against you,

45:58.402 --> 46:00.645
How do you defend an accusation?

46:02.748 --> 46:10.139
You have to be right with the Lord, and you have to go, though you slay me, yet will I praise you.

46:11.341 --> 46:15.367
Regardless of what this situation is, I'm not going.

46:15.387 --> 46:25.783
1 Peter 2, 19 speaks to that, by the way, for this is commendable if because of conscience towards God, one endures grief, suffering wrongly.

46:26.524 --> 46:27.986
Okay, you blew it.

46:28.322 --> 46:29.543
You deserve the grief.

46:30.525 --> 46:35.571
For what credit is it if, when you are beaten for your faults, you take it patiently?

46:36.212 --> 46:41.938
But when you do good and suffer, if you take it patiently, this is commendable before God.

46:42.379 --> 46:49.387
For to this you were called because Christ also suffered for us, leaving us an example that you should follow.

46:49.468 --> 46:51.049
He just makes it clear.

46:51.090 --> 46:58.098
There's something deeper when you endure

46:58.178 --> 47:00.622
even when you did what was right.

47:01.042 --> 47:08.634
Verse 21, but the Lord was with Joseph and showed him mercy and he gave him favor in the sight of the keeper.

47:08.674 --> 47:11.758
The prison sets us up into next week.

47:11.999 --> 47:12.860
This is amazing.

47:13.020 --> 47:27.442
He comes into the house as a slave, he's faithful, endures temptation year after year probably, comes out victorious, goes in the prison and if anyone could sulk and say, I'm done, I'm done.

47:27.938 --> 47:35.588
Here God puts him in and brings him this great opportunity and Joseph just leans into it.

47:35.608 --> 47:40.514
You know, this is, contentment is not getting what I want, it's wanting what I get.

47:40.554 --> 47:43.157
This is what you gave me, this is what you want.

47:43.418 --> 47:49.125
And here's what I think the power of Joseph's life is he never let go of his dream.

47:50.587 --> 47:56.114
He knew this is the vision that God gave and he can't fail on what he said he was gonna do.

47:56.738 --> 48:03.912
And therefore, whatever he has, I'm going to take it that you're doing to work and doing something in and through me.

48:04.553 --> 48:11.206
And so isn't it amazing what we can endure when we're right with the Lord?

48:13.370 --> 48:15.835
When I know, you know what, Lord, I'm walking with you.

48:15.875 --> 48:16.696
I'm faithful.

48:16.796 --> 48:17.618
I'm obedient.

48:17.954 --> 48:23.783
Even though all these things may seem to be against me, I can endure it all because I know that you're with me."

48:24.264 --> 48:31.315
And here he is enduring because the presence of the Lord with him even in the home now in the prison.

48:31.656 --> 48:33.419
And we close verse 22 and 23.

48:35.302 --> 48:38.066
And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph.

48:39.074 --> 48:45.164
Joseph's hand, all the prisoners who were in the prison, whatever they did there, it was his doing.

48:45.565 --> 48:57.084
The keeper of the prison did not look into anything that was under Joseph's authority because the Lord was with him, and whatever he did, the Lord made it prosper.

48:58.866 --> 49:00.970
What an amazing young man.

49:01.030 --> 49:03.133
God has a calling.

49:03.935 --> 49:05.938
God has a plan.

49:06.402 --> 49:14.575
Satan is coming for a shot to take him down, but this young man indoors through it as we look at these things.

49:15.056 --> 49:20.484
And I just find it so amazing.

49:20.504 --> 49:25.933
I have never, I've never been out of the pulpit three weeks in a row.

49:26.393 --> 49:27.014
That was tough.

49:28.657 --> 49:29.298
Down dune.

49:29.666 --> 49:31.408
disaster relief in North Carolina.

49:31.428 --> 49:32.230
That was a plan.

49:32.830 --> 49:35.795
Then Yossi, Pastor Yossi, comes into town from Israel.

49:35.835 --> 49:37.297
Man can't miss that opportunity.

49:37.697 --> 49:42.124
Then Pastor David cruising through on his way to Pakistan said, man, I can't miss that.

49:42.464 --> 49:43.846
But isn't it interesting?

49:43.886 --> 49:47.872
Orlando did a great job in his teaching.

49:48.352 --> 49:50.756
I was here for Yossi and David.

49:51.357 --> 49:53.740
Isn't it interesting what their messages were?

49:55.202 --> 49:57.906
Let everything that you do do for the glory of God.

49:58.722 --> 50:05.129
Romans 12, 1 and 2, I beseech you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God that you present your bodies a living sacrifice.

50:05.509 --> 50:07.992
Holy, acceptable to God, which is your reasonable service.

50:08.312 --> 50:15.159
Do not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind that you may prove what is good, acceptable, and perfect will of God.

50:15.179 --> 50:18.022
Their message was just a living sacrifice.

50:18.042 --> 50:20.925
And I love how David ended his message last week.

50:20.965 --> 50:25.650
He took out a blank piece of paper and says, you know, we always write our story.

50:26.658 --> 50:29.522
And again, if we look at Joseph, he would have never wrote this story.

50:30.503 --> 50:39.956
But you know, there's this power as the living sacrifice where we have this blank sheet of paper and we hand it to the Lord and go write your story in my life.

50:41.157 --> 50:42.499
I'm your living sacrifice.

50:43.661 --> 50:47.506
And I will do what you call me to do and whatever I do.

50:47.810 --> 50:53.539
I'll do it for your glory in the tasking that you give me in the temptations that arise and come daily.

50:53.559 --> 50:55.201
I'm going to give you glory in those things.

50:55.562 --> 51:04.936
And even when I earn to a trowel and maybe it's by innocence and not of my own doing in the middle, I'm going to give you glory so that you might be glorified.

51:05.537 --> 51:07.540
And that's when the Lord takes us.

51:08.121 --> 51:10.204
We're more than an instrument in the vessel.

51:10.484 --> 51:15.752
We become a tool in his hand to shape and work in a lost and dying world.

51:16.113 --> 51:17.074
And then I love it.

51:17.186 --> 51:33.013
like Joseph, we become this weapon that beats down and defeats all the lies of the world and all the lies of the devil and all the lies of the flesh because we showed what God can do when we are in his hand and in his presence.

51:33.113 --> 51:37.441
Father, we bless you and we thank you for this word that you gave us.

51:37.921 --> 51:42.930
We see an amazing God with an amazing love that

51:44.610 --> 51:54.281
Though maybe we don't understand all these things that are going on, we'll take your presence over any place in this world.

51:55.602 --> 52:01.769
Lord, all of us would rather be nowhere else except in your presence.

52:02.810 --> 52:06.314
And when we're in your presence, Lord, it's amazing what we can endure.

52:06.354 --> 52:13.522
It's amazing what we can do because we know when we're right with you what we can overcome.

52:14.402 --> 52:17.045
And like Joseph, what a witness and what a story.

52:17.506 --> 52:18.487
And I pray that for us.

52:18.847 --> 52:39.030
I don't think anyone's immune from anything in this passage today, whether it's in the tasking of where you put us or the temptation of the lies that Satan wants to present to follow after or just the trowel of living godly lives in the midst of a fallen world.

52:39.871 --> 52:42.354
But you've got something that you're doing.

52:42.754 --> 52:50.245
You did it with this young man, and there's not one of us that you're not doing something with in our sphere that you've put us.

52:50.966 --> 52:54.912
Joseph couldn't reach Pasadena or Glen Burney, but we can.

52:55.633 --> 53:02.343
And wherever you have us, the workplaces, the schoolyards, the ball field, we can.

53:03.024 --> 53:04.346
So Lord, we thank you.

53:04.386 --> 53:10.034
Would you give your people, give us the power to come and overcome?

53:10.146 --> 53:12.764
and that whatever we do, we do it for your glory.

53:13.146 --> 53:14.898
In your name, amen.

